headline: Why Western Digital (WDC) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of leading data storage manufacturer Western Digital (NASDAQ: WDC) jumped 2.1% in the afternoon session after the company announced a series of next-generation storage solutions aimed at the rapidly growing artificial intelligence (AI) and high-performance computing (HPC) markets. At an industry event, Western Digital showcased its Ultrastar Data60 and Data102 products, which were designed to provide higher storage density and consume less power.
